What if I have a $5 million building that unlike other real estate deals where you have to put down 20-30% up front, you could qualify to have a bank finance 100% of the purchase price? And what if we negotiate with the bank a balloon note with no principal payments for 10 to 15 years and a very competitive interest rate? And, what if I told you that the building and similar properties have an appraised value over the last 25+ years with a cap rate of 7%?  With that leverage you are bound to generate double-digittax-free returns, sometimes as high as 20%. What if I also told you, that after 10 years the building would have enough equity to refinance the loan at a fix guaranteed rate, provide for all future expenses of owning the property, allow for the property to pass to your heirs debt-free and also generate $500,000 in after-tax income every year for the rest of your life‚Ä¶
